'Concluding' is a novel by British writer Henry Green first published in 1948.
It is set entirely on the expansive and idyllic premises of a state-run
institution for girls somewhere in rural England and chronicles the events of
one summer's day—a Wednesday, and "Founder's Day"—in the lives of
the staff, the students, and several other people living on the grounds. During
that day, two girls go missing.
